arity states around 1.5\nMeV as well as of a candidate for a J$^{\\pi}$=5$^-$ state around 2.5 MeV give\nfurther support to the collapse of the N=20 gap and to the inversion between\nthe 0f$\\_{7/2}$ and 1p$\\_{3/2}$ levels below Z=12. These features are discussed\nin the framework of Shell Model and EDF calculations, leading to predicted\nnegative parity states in the low energy spectra of the $^{26}$F and $^{25}$O\nnuclei.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Mar 2015 07:10:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-25"}
